{"author":"greddyforce","permlink":"shots-around-borgarfjordur-eystri","category":"hive-194913","title":"Shots Around Borgarfjörður Eystri","body":"Borgarfjörður Eystri is Iceland's remote northeastern fishing village that has only around 100 people living in total. Yesterday I did a post where I took on a mountain hike nearby to this village. When the hike was done we came back to this village and had a walk around the area to see what there is to see. \n\nI just took random shots of places and landscapes nearby, it's really beautiful there. \n\n\n\n![DSC_0723.jpg](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/EpLf6uVdvmyaynQZZiQotFiYFJ8eLz9WDCd5G61y3UCB1VTSSBJAz6uKM6qW5HxDafg.jpg)\n<hr>\n\n\n![DSC_0720.jpg](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/23r1gN5FwWmUdQ7Nf681XJbw4DXj6H4vwNCnZhT7ypzBFQJEZYEeGRp8Fx1h93N5iDw2p.jpg)\n<hr>\n\n\n![DSC_0722.jpg](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/242rs9RxsA4DLu26M4Xv2GnGJnWtSVLz96HPdEVNornnfwRW4ayyGuVjeKRkwnwsaTKa2.jpg)\n<hr>\n\n\n\n![DSC_0719.jpg](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/242rrwSvmGGQPDJ3nM6EHtvoKXicYHakHzTeTir9CUK4HyWWhwVoPnjzgTV29sjYnE9aG.jpg)\n\nThis is right next to the sea, a rocky coastline. \n\n\n![DSC_0728.jpg](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/23zS5EofLLiqXS3iWt1g1abyGko9L3RCr2tJ7BP1mtrE6YUFnYGw1ytT2K31hKHxhHSx9.jpg)\n<hr>\n\n\n![DSC_0730.jpg](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/244ob2iLMPsShZt93cVgKfW8NDiotGh48buztN8H2xqWcR9gSvP8i2LXDjPLc2yb2TuJo.jpg)\n<hr>\n\n\n![DSC_0732.jpg](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/244UjmZZ95qBmEcWb76hrtYY4kA3KrHmBVWzarAisega9PDvasDUztuH1w3Davgsa2DcH.jpg)\n<hr>\n\nHere you can see basically everything, this is how large the Borgarfjörður Eystri is.\n\n![DSC_0733.jpg](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/244KPG2Ny7hrNQkELcd61CcCLpuYnh7M8HeZnqGmbzfFYtqJysuj81sEZRAfUk6UWuWog.jpg)\n\nView straight over the sea. This is where I started a mountain hike in the previous post.\n\n\n![DSC_0729.jpg](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/23zkeBhYKPULtXQSY6dAScrmESyK1M9pFib57LMHs2ZLAionL6SBEE53kuxyeoGu9qBj6.jpg)\n\nSaw some strangely shaped cloud overhead. \n\n\n![DSC_0734.jpg](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/23xyJkneEwkUdT5KLL5KnqKaVTeJV96DCvPufgr4UQAPCyqBKDXFVRz6JFf8fdU4uLcWG.jpg)\n\nOriginal Icelandic housing.\n\n\n![DSC_0736.jpg](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/244A2fkSGrx6VfahQyEWYYtwrDBxcuDiyZyVXH8fNsynQzLuqnVzqY3HHPNGVkxv4VQY1.jpg)\n\nLocal church.\n\n\n![DSC_0737.jpg](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/243zZReVX9dSiUb1yabojJzRpKPTd4WVM457ConNL14eD7z5NiRavmjRJxk4dai3X5ueq.jpg)\n\nNear our campsite was a small hill. Of course, we decided to conquer it. \n\n\n![DSC_0738.jpg](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/242Y3cwEqzFtoZRwUU7pCGUsBDQp1mEEMMnMeD9szsym6H7KuNThRTB2ixyHo9G44Cudv.jpg)\n\n\n\nI really liked being in this area. The hike in a previous post and the Village area here is something else. Almost no tourists what I like the most and absolutely beautiful nature all around. Definitely give it a visit when traveling in Iceland. It's off the beaten path but if you have time then go for it. \n<hr>\n<hr>\n<hr>\n\n\n![Untitled-1.png](https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/23u5VN6XENde9DSvzdcACoMgKaT9ZK3mbu7c1inRiAZcyURePubm2E6XM8UcnQ4c3XSgQ.png)\n\n\n\n\n\n[//]:# (!pinmapple 65.524138 lat -13.800832 long  d3scr)\n\n\n\n","json_metadata":"{\"app\":\"peakd/2021.09.1\",\"format\":\"markdown\",\"tags\":[\"phtoography\",\"travel\",\"iceland\",\"nature\",\"blog\",\"life\",\"village\",\"landscape\",\"exploration\"],\"users\":[],\"image\":[\"https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/EpLf6uVdvmyaynQZZiQotFiYFJ8eLz9WDCd5G61y3UCB1VTSSBJAz6uKM6qW5HxDafg.jpg\",\"https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyforce/23r1gN5FwWmUdQ7Nf681XJbw4DXj6H4vwNCnZhT7ypzBFQJEZYEeGRp8Fx1h93N5iDw2p.jpg\",\"https://files.peakd.com/file/peakd-hive/greddyf